      {
        "question": "Which Node.js version do we need for Angular 19?",
        "answer": "Angular 19 officially supports Node.js 18 LTS and newer. Verify the CI/CD pipeline uses at least Node.js 18; upgrade the local development environment accordingly."
      },
      {
        "question": "Do we have to upgrade TypeScript as part of this upgrade?",
        "answer": "Yes. Angular 19 requires TypeScript 5.0 or higher. The current project uses TypeScript 4.9.5, so the tsconfig and any type‑dependent code must be updated to the newer compiler."
      },
      {
        "question": "Are there breaking API changes in Angular 19 that could affect our code?",
        "answer": "Angular 19 deprecates several APIs that were still present in 18 (e.g., certain lifecycle hooks and deprecated router methods). Review the Angular migration guide for v19 and run the Angular update schematic; it will flag usages that need refactoring."
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the status of the vertical action bar after the upgrade?",
        "answer": "The vertical action bar is deprecated but remains supported until PL 13.2.0. After moving to PL 12.6.0 it must still function; no removal is required now, but future upgrades should plan for its replacement."
      },
      {
        "question": "Will our current versions of ng‑bootstrap, ng‑select, and ag‑grid work with Angular 19?",
        "answer": "Compatibility must be verified against each library’s release notes. The ticket notes a specific patch for ng‑bootstrap that must be kept, indicating that the out‑of‑the‑box version may not be compatible. Check the latest versions of ng‑bootstrap, ng‑select, and ag‑grid that declare Angular 19 support and apply the required patch."
      }
    ],
